general.description: Felling's Over-the-Road Series Step Deck Trailer are Ready for the Long Haul Transport your loads with confidence when you are pulling a Felling Step Deck Trailer. Plus these models are standard with rub rail & stake pockets with double pipe spools to make securing any load easier.

general.description: Hydraulic Tail Trailer - Perimeter Frame Trailer (PF-HT) Felling's Hydraulic Tail Trailer - Perimeter Frame trailers are ideal for those in the Commercial Transport, Construction, Implement, and Rental industries. This trailer provides the user with the flexibility to transport multiple pieces of small equipment or one to two large pieces. Felling's hydraulic folding tail drop deck trailer design also provides ease in the loading of low clearance machines like rollers, scissor lifts, and aerial lifts, with a six-degree (6o) break-over at the end of the main deck. The hydraulic tail provides the operator with the capability of dock loading up to 60'' high. Standard with an 8' 6'' hydraulic tail with 4' Fold Under (Star Plate Center/Traction Bars Outer Over Tread Plate).

general.description: When details matter, there's only One choice in Deckover Equipment Trailers...Felling We know that you work hard and expect your equipment to do the same and then some. That's why we have designed and engineered our Deckover Equipment Trailers with the strength and durability to get the job done day after day. Offering Medium to Heavy Duty Low Profile Deckover tagalong trailers, Felling has the right flatbed trailer for your equipment hauling needs.

features: *Medium Duty Deck-Over Equipment Trailers Listed Below Low Profile Models

The Low Profile deck over tag design delivers a 33'' loaded deck height, providing operators with load versatility and ease of use with loading low clearance equipment. Constructed with a fabricated/ engineered main frame beams which are pierced for the cross members to be inserted through, producing the lower deck height.
FT-50-3 LP FT-60-3 LP *Models also available in Stacked Frame Design
Felling Trailers, Inc. is an ISO 9001:2015 Certified Quality Management System Company, and is WBENC-Certified WBE.
options: Air Ramp option can be equipped on Felling's 20,000 lb Deck-Over tag trailers all the way up to our Semi-Trailer models.
Hydraulic Powered Ramps option can be equipped on Felling's 20,000 lb Deck-Over tag trailers all the way up to our Semi-Trailer models.

general.description: Felling's Utility Cable Reel trailers are built to your specification with safety-minded features. Load capacities ranging from 1,890 lbs. to 14,000 lbs, a wide range of reel capacities, LED lighting and sealed wiring harness are all standard. With options like the Self Loading Turret Reel that offers a 360 degree hydraulically operated rotating turret assembly, the turret can lock into any position when the directional control valve is released. To our Hydraulic Payout/Take-Up Rim Drive assembly, that will drive reels from 20" up to 120" dia. drive wheel engagement is accomplished with a hydraulic cylinder, various reel widths capable. Felling has your Utility Cable Real needs covered.

general.description: Felling Has Been Serving the Utility/Telecom Industry for Over 40 Years. Some jobs call for standard Felling Utility Pole Trailers and then there are those that call for one to be built to your customized spec with safety-minded features. Take confidence in knowing we have been supplying both our standard and highly customized Utility Pole and Utility Pole / Cargo Trailers for over 4 decades to the Utility/Telecom Industry. Felling's Utility Pole trailers have filled the pole transport needs of Electrical Coops across the country from large to small fleets. Horizontal Directional Drill Trailer Series Fellings' Horizontal Directional Drill Trailers are used to transport directional boring machines known as horizontal directional drills (HDD), used for horizontal underground drilling/directional boring. HDD is a minimal impact trenchless method of installing underground utilities such as pipes, conduits, or cables. Felling offers two classes of HDD trailers; Drop Deck I Drill Series, deck between the wheels, models with 12K-27K capacities and Low Pro Drill Series, deck-over flatbed tag trailers with 30K-50K capacities.

features: Rubber Torsion Suspension FT-20 I Drill Series FT-24 I Drill Series
Spring Suspension FT-20 I-S Drill Series FT-24 I-S Drill Series

The deck-over drill series provides the same with the double incline beavertail that reduces the top break over in half. Standard Features include 6' Double Incline Beavertail, 6' x 20'' Self Cleaning Angle Iron Spring Assist Ramps, Jack - 140K Twin 2-Speed, and more.
Featured Unit - FT-24 I Drill Package Loading a Horizontal Directional Drill Trailer on a Felling Deck-Over Trailer
options: Felling's drop-deck drill models provide an ideal incline with a gradual slope eliminating the need for dunnage. Built with the properly placed cross-members, D-Rings, and ramps for your HDD. In addition to a robust build, Felling offers drill kit options engineered specifically for your model of horizontal directional drill.

general.description: Horizontal Directional Drill Trailer Series Fellings' Horizontal Directional Drill Trailers are used to transport directional boring machines known as horizontal directional drills (HDD), used for horizontal underground drilling/directional boring.
